5.1 The Source is provided "as is" and any express or implied warranties, including, but not limited to, implied warranties of merchantability, of satisfactory quality, of fitness for a particular purpose, and non-infringement of third party rights are disclaimed. In no event shall the Licensor or any Contributors be liable for any direct, indirect, incidental, special, exemplary, or consequential damages (including, but not limited to, procurement of substitute goods or services, loss of use, data, or profits, or business interruption) however caused and on any theory of liability, whether in contract, strict liability, or tort (including negligence or otherwise) arising in any way out of the use of the Source or Product, even if advised of the possibility of such damage.

5.2 You are solely responsible for ensuring that your use of the Source does not infringe any third party's intellectual property rights. If you distribute a Product or Derivative, you agree to indemnify the Licensor and any Contributors for any liability, damages, and costs (including reasonable legal fees) arising from your use, modification, or distribution of the Source or Product which results in infringement of any third party's intellectual property rights.

6 Patents

6.1 You are granted a licence to those patent claims owned by the Licensor that are necessarily infringed by the Source, Derivative, or Product.

6.2 If you institute patent litigation against any entity (including a cross-claim or counterclaim in a lawsuit) alleging that the Source or a Product directly or indirectly infringes any patent, then all rights granted to you under this Licence shall terminate as of the date such litigation is filed.

